     3έΗΤAll notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.
    11έΗΤ## [14.0.3] (2026-01-31)
    12έΗΤ
    13έΗΤ### Added
    14έΗΤ
    15έΗΤ- Release Policy document ([#2462])
    17έΗΤ### Changes
    18έΗΤ
    19έΗΤ- old major versions now supported for 12 months instead of just previous major version, to give predictable end-of-life date ([#2462])
    20έΗΤ- clarify typing for deprecated callback parameter to `.outputHelp()` ([#2427])
    21έΗΤ- simple readability improvements to README ([#2465])
    23έΗΤ## [14.0.2] (2025-10-25)
    24έΗΤ
    25έΗΤ### Changed
    26έΗΤ
    27έΗΤ- improve negative number auto-detection test ([#2428])
    28έΗΤ- update (dev) dependencies
    30έΗΤ## [14.0.1] (2025-09-12)
    31έΗΤ
    32έΗΤ### Fixed
    33έΗΤ
    34έΗΤ- broken markdown link in README ([#2369])
    36έΗΤ### Changed
    37έΗΤ
    38έΗΤ- improve code readability by using optional chaining ([#2394])
    39έΗΤ- use more idiomatic code with object spread instead of `Object.assign()` ([#2395])
    40έΗΤ- improve code readability using `string.endsWith()` instead of `string.slice()` ([#2396])
    41έΗΤ- refactor `.parseOptions()` to process args array in-place ([#2409])
    42έΗΤ- change private variadic support routines from `._concatValue()` to `._collectValue()` (change code from `array.concat()` to `array.push()`) ([#2410])
    43έΗΤ- update (dev) dependencies
    45έΗΤ## [14.0.0] (2025-05-18)
    46έΗΤ
    47έΗΤ### Added
    48έΗΤ
    49έΗΤ- support for groups of options and commands in the help using low-level `.helpGroup()` on `Option` and `Command`, and higher-level `.optionsGroup()` and `.commandsGroup()` which can be used in chaining way to specify group title for following options/commands ([#2328])
    50έΗΤ- support for unescaped negative numbers as option-arguments and command-arguments ([#2339])
    51έΗΤ- TypeScript: add `parseArg` property to `Argument` class ([#2359])
    53έΗΤ### Fixed
    54έΗΤ
    55έΗΤ- remove bogus leading space in help when option has default value but not a description ([#2348])
    56έΗΤ- `.configureOutput()` now makes copy of settings instead of modifying in-place, fixing side-effects ([#2350])
    58έΗΤ### Changed
    59έΗΤ
    60έΗΤ- *Breaking:* Commander 14 requires Node.js v20 or higher
    61έΗΤ- internal refactor of `Help` class adding `.formatItemList()` and `.groupItems()` methods ([#2328])
    63έΗΤ## [13.1.0] (2025-01-21)
    64έΗΤ
    65έΗΤ### Added
    66έΗΤ
    67έΗΤ- support a pair of long option flags to allow a memorable shortened flag, like `.option('--ws, --workspace')` ([#2312])
    69έΗΤ## [13.0.0] (2024-12-30)
    70έΗΤ
    71έΗΤ### Added
    72έΗΤ
    73έΗΤ- support multiple calls to `.parse()` with default settings ([#2299])
    74έΗΤ- add `.saveStateBeforeParse()` and `.restoreStateBeforeParse()` for use by subclasses ([#2299])
    75έΗΤ- style routines like `styleTitle()` to add color to help using `.configureHelp()` or Help subclass ([#2251])
    76έΗΤ- color related support in `.configureOutput()` for `getOutHasColors()`, `getErrHasColors()`, and `stripColor()` ([#2251])
    77έΗΤ- Help property for `minWidthToWrap` ([#2251])
    78έΗΤ- Help methods for `displayWidth()`, `boxWrap()`, `preformatted()` et al ([#2251])
    80έΗΤ### Changed
    81έΗΤ
    82έΗΤ- *Breaking*: excess command-arguments cause an error by default, see migration tips ([#2223])
    83έΗΤ- *Breaking*: throw during Option construction for unsupported option flags, like multiple characters after single `-` ([#2270])
    84έΗΤ  - note: support for dual long option flags added in Commander 13.1
    85έΗΤ- *Breaking*: throw on multiple calls to `.parse()` if `storeOptionsAsProperties: true` ([#2299])
    86έΗΤ- TypeScript: include implicit `this` in parameters for action handler callback ([#2197])
    88έΗΤ### Deleted
    89έΗΤ
    90έΗΤ- *Breaking*: `Help.wrap()` refactored into `formatItem()` and `boxWrap()` ([#2251])
    92έΗΤ### Migration Tips
    93έΗΤ
    94έΗΤ**Excess command-arguments**
