   365έΗΤ## [9.0.0] (2022-01-28)
   366έΗΤ
   367έΗΤ### Added
   368έΗΤ
   369έΗΤ- simpler ECMAScript import ([#1589])
   370έΗΤ- Option.preset() allows specifying value/arg for option when used without option-argument (especially optional, but also boolean option) ([#1652])
   371έΗΤ- `.executableDir()` for custom search for subcommands ([#1571])
   372έΗΤ- throw with helpful message if pass `Option` to `.option()` or `.requiredOption()` ([#1655])
   373έΗΤ- .`error()` for generating errors from client code just like Commander generated errors, with support for  `.configureOutput()`, `.exitOverride()`, and `.showHelpAfterError()` ([#1675])
   374έΗΤ- `.optsWithGlobals()` to return merged local and global options ([#1671])
   376έΗΤ### Changed
   377έΗΤ
   378έΗΤ- *Breaking:* Commander 9 requires Node.js v12.20.0 or higher
   379έΗΤ- update package-lock.json to lockfile@2 format ([#1659])
   380έΗΤ- `showSuggestionAfterError` is now on by default ([#1657])
   381έΗΤ- *Breaking:* default value specified for boolean option now always used as default value (see .preset() to match some previous behaviours) ([#1652])
   382έΗΤ- default value for boolean option only shown in help if true/false ([#1652])
   383έΗΤ- use command name as prefix for subcommand stand-alone executable name (with fallback to script name for backwards compatibility) ([#1571])
   384έΗΤ- allow absolute path with `executableFile` ([#1571])
   385έΗΤ- removed restriction that nested subcommands must specify `executableFile` ([#1571])
   386έΗΤ- TypeScript: allow passing readonly string array to `.choices()` ([#1667])
   387έΗΤ- TypeScript: allow passing readonly string array to `.parse()`, `.parseAsync()`, `.aliases()` ([#1669])
   389έΗΤ### Fixed
   390έΗΤ
   391έΗΤ- option with optional argument not supplied on command line now works when option already has a value, whether from default value or from previous arguments ([#1652])
   393έΗΤ### Removed
   394έΗΤ
   395έΗΤ- *Breaking:* removed internal fallback to `require.main.filename` when script not known from arguments passed to `.parse()` (can supply details using `.name()`, and `.executableDir()` or `executableFile`) ([#1571])
