   535έΗΤ## [7.1.0] (2021-02-15)
   536έΗΤ
   537έΗΤ### Added
   538έΗΤ
   539έΗΤ- support for named imports from ECMAScript modules ([#1440])
   540έΗΤ- add `.cjs` to list of expected script file extensions ([#1449])
   541έΗΤ- allow using option choices and variadic together ([#1454])
   543έΗΤ### Fixed
   544έΗΤ
   545έΗΤ- replace use of deprecated `process.mainModule` ([#1448])
   546έΗΤ- regression for legacy `command('*')` and call when command line includes options ([#1464])
   547έΗΤ- regression for `on('command:*', ...)` and call when command line includes unknown options ([#1464])
   548έΗΤ- display best error for combination of unknown command and unknown option (i.e. unknown command) ([#1464])
   550έΗΤ### Changed
   551έΗΤ
   552έΗΤ- make TypeScript typings tests stricter ([#1453])
   553έΗΤ- improvements to README and tests
   555έΗΤ## [7.0.0] (2021-01-15)
   556έΗΤ
   557έΗΤ### Added
   558έΗΤ
   559έΗΤ- `.enablePositionalOptions()` to let program and subcommand reuse same option ([#1427])
   560έΗΤ- `.passThroughOptions()` to pass options through to other programs without needing `--` ([#1427])
   561έΗΤ- `.allowExcessArguments(false)` to show an error message if there are too many command-arguments on command line for the action handler ([#1409])
   562έΗΤ- `.configureOutput()` to modify use of stdout and stderr or customise display of errors ([#1387])
   563έΗΤ- use `.addHelpText()` to add text before or after the built-in help, for just current command or also for all subcommands ([#1296])
   564έΗΤ- enhance Option class ([#1331])
   565έΗΤ  - allow hiding options from help
   566έΗΤ  - allow restricting option arguments to a list of choices
   567έΗΤ  - allow setting how default value is shown in help
   568έΗΤ- `.createOption()` to support subclassing of automatically created options (like `.createCommand()`) ([#1380])
   569έΗΤ- refactor the code generating the help into a separate public Help class ([#1365])
   570έΗΤ  - support sorting subcommands and options in help
   571έΗΤ  - support specifying wrap width (columns)
   572έΗΤ  - allow subclassing Help class
   573έΗΤ  - allow configuring Help class without subclassing
   575έΗΤ### Changed
   576έΗΤ
   577έΗΤ- *Breaking:* options are stored safely by default, not as properties on the command ([#1409])
   578έΗΤ  - this especially affects accessing options on program, use `program.opts()`
   579έΗΤ  - revert behaviour with `.storeOptionsAsProperties()`
   580έΗΤ- *Breaking:* action handlers are passed options and command separately ([#1409])
   581έΗΤ- deprecated callback parameter to `.help()` and `.outputHelp()` (removed from README) ([#1296])
   582έΗΤ- *Breaking:* errors now displayed using `process.stderr.write()` instead of `console.error()`
   583έΗΤ- deprecate `.on('--help')` (removed from README) ([#1296])
   584έΗΤ- initialise the command description to empty string (previously undefined) ([#1365])
   585έΗΤ- document and annotate deprecated routines ([#1349])
   587έΗΤ### Fixed
   588έΗΤ
   589έΗΤ- wrapping bugs in help ([#1365])
   590έΗΤ  - first line of command description was wrapping two characters early
   591έΗΤ  - pad width calculation was not including help option and help command
   592έΗΤ  - pad width calculation was including hidden options and commands
   593έΗΤ- improve backwards compatibility for custom command event listeners ([#1403])
   595έΗΤ### Deleted
   596έΗΤ
   597έΗΤ- *Breaking:* `.passCommandToAction()` ([#1409])
   598έΗΤ  - no longer needed as action handler is passed options and command
   599έΗΤ- *Breaking:* "extra arguments" parameter to action handler ([#1409])
   600έΗΤ  - if being used to detect excess arguments, there is now an error available by setting `.allowExcessArguments(false)`
   602έΗΤ### Migration Tips
   603έΗΤ
   604έΗΤThe biggest change is the parsed option values. Previously the options were stored by default as properties on the command object, and now the options are stored separately.
