   705έΗΤ## [6.1.0] (2020-08-28)
   706έΗΤ
   707έΗΤ### Added
   708έΗΤ
   709έΗΤ- include URL to relevant section of README for error for potential conflict between Command properties and option values ([#1306])
   710έΗΤ- `.combineFlagAndOptionalValue(false)` to ease upgrade path from older versions of Commander ([#1326])
   711έΗΤ- allow disabling the built-in help option using `.helpOption(false)` ([#1325])
   712έΗΤ- allow just some arguments in `argumentDescription` to `.description()` ([#1323])
   714έΗΤ### Changed
   715έΗΤ
   716έΗΤ- tidy async test and remove lint override ([#1312])
   718έΗΤ### Fixed
   719έΗΤ
   720έΗΤ- executable subcommand launching when script path not known ([#1322])
   722έΗΤ## [6.0.0] (2020-07-21)
   723έΗΤ
   724έΗΤ### Added
   725έΗΤ
   726έΗΤ- add support for variadic options ([#1250])
   727έΗΤ- allow options to be added with just a short flag ([#1256])
   728έΗΤ  - *Breaking* the option property has same case as flag. e.g. flag `-n` accessed as `opts().n` (previously uppercase)
   729έΗΤ- *Breaking* throw an error if there might be a clash between option name and a Command property, with advice on how to resolve ([#1275])
   731έΗΤ### Fixed
   732έΗΤ
   733έΗΤ- Options which contain -no- in the middle of the option flag should not be treated as negatable. ([#1301])
   735έΗΤ## [6.0.0-0] (2020-06-20)
   736έΗΤ
   737έΗΤ(Released in 6.0.0)
   739έΗΤ## [5.1.0] (2020-04-25)
   740έΗΤ
   741έΗΤ### Added
   742έΗΤ
   743έΗΤ- support for multiple command aliases, the first of which is shown in the auto-generated help ([#531], [#1236])
   744έΗΤ- configuration support in `addCommand()` for `hidden` and `isDefault` ([#1232])
   746έΗΤ### Fixed
   747έΗΤ
   748έΗΤ- omit masked help flags from the displayed help ([#645], [#1247])
   749έΗΤ- remove old short help flag when change help flags using `helpOption` ([#1248])
   751έΗΤ### Changed
   752έΗΤ
   753έΗΤ- remove use of `arguments` to improve auto-generated help in editors ([#1235])
   754έΗΤ- rename `.command()` configuration `noHelp` to `hidden` (but not remove old support) ([#1232])
   755έΗΤ- improvements to documentation
   756έΗΤ- update dependencies
   757έΗΤ- update tested versions of node
   758έΗΤ- eliminate lint errors in TypeScript ([#1208])
   760έΗΤ## [5.0.0] (2020-03-14)
   761έΗΤ
   762έΗΤ### Added
   763έΗΤ
   764έΗΤ* support for nested commands with action-handlers ([#1] [#764] [#1149])
   765έΗΤ* `.addCommand()` for adding a separately configured command ([#764] [#1149])
   766έΗΤ* allow a non-executable to be set as the default command ([#742] [#1149])
   767έΗΤ* implicit help command when there are subcommands (previously only if executables) ([#1149])
   768έΗΤ* customise implicit help command with `.addHelpCommand()` ([#1149])
   769έΗΤ* display error message for unknown subcommand, by default ([#432] [#1088] [#1149])
   770έΗΤ* display help for missing subcommand, by default ([#1088] [#1149])
   771έΗΤ* combined short options as single argument may include boolean flags and value flag and value (e.g. `-a -b -p 80` can be written as `-abp80`) ([#1145])
   772έΗΤ* `.parseOption()` includes short flag and long flag expansions ([#1145])
   773έΗΤ* `.helpInformation()` returns help text as a string, previously a private routine ([#1169])
   774έΗΤ* `.parse()` implicitly uses `process.argv` if arguments not specified ([#1172])
   775έΗΤ* optionally specify where `.parse()` arguments "from", if not following node conventions ([#512] [#1172])
   776έΗΤ* suggest help option along with unknown command error ([#1179])
   777έΗΤ* TypeScript definition for `commands` property of `Command` ([#1184])
   778έΗΤ* export `program` property ([#1195])
   779έΗΤ* `createCommand` factory method to simplify subclassing ([#1191])
   781έΗΤ### Fixed
   782έΗΤ
   783έΗΤ* preserve argument order in subcommands ([#508] [#962] [#1138])
   784έΗΤ* do not emit `command:*` for executable subcommands ([#809] [#1149])
   785έΗΤ* action handler called whether or not there are non-option arguments ([#1062] [#1149])
   786έΗΤ* combining option short flag and value in single argument now works for subcommands ([#1145])
   787έΗΤ* only add implicit help command when it will not conflict with other uses of argument ([#1153] [#1149])
   788έΗΤ* implicit help command works with command aliases ([#948] [#1149])
   789έΗΤ* options are validated whether or not there is an action handler ([#1149])
   791έΗΤ### Changed
   792έΗΤ
   793έΗΤ* *Breaking* `.args` contains command arguments with just recognised options removed ([#1032] [#1138])
   794έΗΤ* *Breaking* display error if required argument for command is missing ([#995] [#1149])
   795έΗΤ* tighten TypeScript definition of custom option processing function passed to `.option()` ([#1119])
   796έΗΤ* *Breaking* `.allowUnknownOption()` ([#802] [#1138])
   797έΗΤ  * unknown options included in arguments passed to command action handler
   798έΗΤ  * unknown options included in `.args`
   799έΗΤ* only recognised option short flags and long flags are expanded (e.g. `-ab` or `--foo=bar`) ([#1145])
   800έΗΤ* *Breaking* `.parseOptions()` ([#1138])
   801έΗΤ  * `args` in returned result renamed `operands` and does not include anything after first unknown option
   802έΗΤ  * `unknown` in returned result has arguments after first unknown option including operands, not just options and values
   803έΗΤ* *Breaking* `.on('command:*', callback)` and other command events passed (changed) results from `.parseOptions`, i.e. operands and unknown  ([#1138])
   804έΗΤ* refactor Option from prototype to class ([#1133])
   805έΗΤ* refactor Command from prototype to class ([#1159])
   806έΗΤ* changes to error handling ([#1165])
   807έΗΤ  * throw for author error, not just display message
   808έΗΤ  * preflight for variadic error
   809έΗΤ  * add tips to missing subcommand executable
   810έΗΤ* TypeScript fluent return types changed to be more subclass friendly, return `this` rather than `Command` ([#1180])
   811έΗΤ* `.parseAsync` returns `Promise<this>` to be consistent with `.parse()` ([#1180])
   812έΗΤ* update dependencies
   814έΗΤ### Removed
   815έΗΤ
   816έΗΤ* removed EventEmitter from TypeScript definition for Command, eliminating implicit peer dependency on `@types/node` ([#1146])
   817έΗΤ* removed private function `normalize` (the functionality has been integrated into `parseOptions`) ([#1145])
   818έΗΤ* `parseExpectedArgs` is now private ([#1149])
   820έΗΤ### Migration Tips
   821έΗΤ
   822έΗΤIf you use `.on('command:*')` or more complicated tests to detect an unrecognised subcommand, you may be able to delete the code and rely on the default behaviour.
