   945έΗΤ## [3.0.1] (2019-08-30)
   946έΗΤ
   947έΗΤ### Added
   948έΗΤ
   949έΗΤ* .name and .usage to README ([#1010])
   950έΗΤ* Table of Contents to README ([#1010])
   951έΗΤ* TypeScript definition for `executableFile` in CommandOptions ([#1028])
   953έΗΤ### Changed
   954έΗΤ
   955έΗΤ* consistently use `const` rather than `var` in README ([#1026])
   957έΗΤ### Fixed
   958έΗΤ
   959έΗΤ* help for sub commands with custom executableFile ([#1018])
   961έΗΤ## [3.0.0] / 2019-08-08
   962έΗΤ
   963έΗΤ* Add option to specify executable file name ([#999])
   964έΗΤ  * e.g. `.command('clone', 'clone description', { executableFile: 'myClone' })`
   965έΗΤ* Change docs for `.command` to contrast action handler vs git-style executable. ([#938] [#990])
   966έΗΤ* **Breaking** Change TypeScript to use overloaded function for `.command`. ([#938] [#990])
   967έΗΤ* Change to use straight quotes around strings in error messages (like 'this' instead of `this') ([#915])
   968έΗΤ* Add TypeScript "reference types" for node ([#974])
   969έΗΤ* Add support for hyphen as an option argument in subcommands ([#697])
   970έΗΤ* Add support for a short option flag and its value to be concatenated for action handler subcommands ([#599])
   971έΗΤ  * e.g. `-p 80` can also be supplied as `-p80`
   972έΗΤ* Add executable arguments to spawn in win32, for git-style executables ([#611])
   973έΗΤ  * e.g. `node --harmony myCommand.js clone`
   974έΗΤ* Add parent command as prefix of subcommand in help ([#980])
   975έΗΤ* Add optional custom description to `.version` ([#963])
   976έΗΤ  * e.g. `program.version('0.0.1', '-v, --vers', 'output the current version')`
   977έΗΤ* Add `.helpOption(flags, description)` routine to customise help flags and description ([#963])
   978έΗΤ  * e.g. `.helpOption('-e, --HELP', 'read more information')`
   979έΗΤ* Fix behavior of --no-* options ([#795])
   980έΗΤ  * can now define both `--foo` and `--no-foo`
   981έΗΤ  * **Breaking** custom event listeners: `--no-foo` on cli now emits `option:no-foo` (previously `option:foo`)
   982έΗΤ  * **Breaking** default value: defining `--no-foo` after defining `--foo` leaves the default value unchanged (previously set it to false)
   983έΗΤ  * allow boolean default value, such as from environment ([#987])
   984έΗΤ* Increment inspector port for spawned subcommands ([#991])
   985έΗΤ  * e.g. `node --inspect myCommand.js clone`
   987έΗΤ### Migration Tips
   988έΗΤ
   989έΗΤThe custom event for a negated option like `--no-foo` is `option:no-foo` (previously `option:foo`).
